<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n33017h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n33" href="#n33017h">N33 (VI.B.4)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n33all.htm#n33017h"> 17(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> purdah </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: (EB XXI:659) the curtain which screens women from the sight of men in Eastern countries; a purdah-nashin is a woman who sits behind the curtain; (the term has passed into common Anglo-Indian usage, and to &ldquo;lift the purdah&rdquo; means to reveal a secret)  <br>Note: See also: <a name="n34134h" href="n34all.htm#n34134h">N34 (VI.B.27):134(h)</a> </mm> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15005a" href="c15all.htm#c15005a">VI.C.15:005(a)</a> </mm></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
